org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.components.modellibs.core.transformations

Class ConnectorReification

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.components.modellibs.core.transformations.ConnectorReification
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IM2MTrafoCDP, IM2MTrafo

    public class ConnectorReification
extends Object
implements IM2MTrafoCDP
    This class enables the reification of connectors, i.e. the replacement of a UML connector with an interaction component. Reification is primarily done on the level of a composite class.

      • oppositeConnEnd

        public static org.eclipse.uml2.uml.ConnectorEnd oppositeConnEnd(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Connector connector,
                                                                org.eclipse.uml2.uml.ConnectorEnd myEnd)
        Simple helper function that finds the opposite connector end when one is given. If returns the first connector end that is not equal to the passed one, but results will not be useful in general for n-ary connectors (n!=2)
        Parameters:
        connector - a connector
        myEnd - one end of a connector.
        Returns:
        the connector end that is associated with the "other" end of a connection, i.e. the end that differs from the passed connector end

      • reifyConnector

        public org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property reifyConnector(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class composite,
                                                    org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property connectorPart,
                                                    org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification compositeIS)
                                             throws TransformationException
        Reify a connector already represented in form of a part (useful for n-ary connectors)
        Parameters:
        composite - containing composite in target target model
        connectorPart - Part representing the connector
        compositeIS - target instance specification of the composite passed as 2nd parameter (required for obtaining node allocation and choosing the right implementation. Main use: decide whether a distributed implementation of an interaction component needs to be used)
        Returns:
        The created part within tmComponent that represents the reified connector
        Throws:
        TransformationException

      • reifyConnector

        public org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property reifyConnector(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class composite,
                                                    org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Connector connector,
                                                    org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification compositeIS)
                                             throws TransformationException
        Reify a connector
        Parameters:
        composite - containing composite
        connector - connector within the passed composite. If connector reification is successful, the passed connector will be destroyed (since replaced by a new connector-part-connector combination)
        compositeIS - instance specification of the composite passed as 2nd parameter (required for obtaining node allocation and choosing the right implementation. Main use: decide whether a distributed implementation of an interaction component needs to be used)
        Returns:
        the created part within the composite or null, if no reification could be executed.
        Throws:
        TransformationException

      • connectContainerPorts

        public void connectContainerPorts(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Class composite,
                                  org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property reifiedConnector)
        Components can contain additional ports that are inherited via the container extension. These ports should typically be connected with additional ports of the (reified) connector. This connection is based on equal port types and is done automatically by this function, i.e. it cannot be done by the developer.
        Parameters:
        composite - the composite in which a connector has been reified.
        reifiedConnector - the part associated with the reifiedConnector
